HEADWORD: Embreathement
<hw>Em*breathe"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
breathing in; inspiration.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The special and immediate suggestion, <qex>embreathement</qex>,
and dictation of the Holy Ghost.</q> <rj><qau>W. Lee.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embrew</ent>⟦br⟧
